* You need LTTng utils and kernel running. See here for packages and instructions: 

  https://launchpad.net/~lttng/+archive/ppa

* To run, you need those extra debian packages

  sudo apt-get install cpuburn libswt-cairo-gtk-3.5-jni libswt-gtk-3.5-java junit4 openjdk-6-jdk liblttvtraceread-jni

* You also need the special SWT Chart library on github

  git@github.com:giraldeau/swtchart.git

* Then, generate the traces with the script tests/gen-traces.sh

  ./tests/gen-traces.sh

* Compute the CPU usage for a trace: 

  ./run.sh tests/traces/burn-1x-1sec


